cuisine: Mediterranean
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Quarter @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Zest and halve @lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{3%teaspoon}, @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Arrange cut sides down. Roast on top rack until tender and slightly crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @garlic{1%clove}(minced for aioli), half the lemon zest, and lemon juice to taste. Season with salt.

Place @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} on a #plate{}; season with salt and pepper. Pat @crab cakes{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; gently press both sides into panko to coat. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium heat. Add coated crab cakes and cook until golden brown on first side, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add @butter{1%tablespoon}, flip crab cakes, and cook until golden brown on other side, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together tomatoes, scallions, a drizzle of olive oil, @arugula{2%ounce}, a big squeeze of lemon juice, and remaining lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide crab cakes, salad, and potatoes between plates. Top crab cakes with aioli. Serve any remaining aioli on the side for dipping.